    "The BPAQ-SF was developed to assess four dispositional sub-traits of aggression: physical aggression, verbal aggression, anger, and hostility.",
    "The BPAQ-SF ranges from 1-5, with higher scores indicating greater aggression.",
    "The BPAQ-SF has demonstrated good internal consistency and strong convergent and discriminant validity [87].",
    "The BPAQ-SF demonstrated good internal consistency in the present sample (α Pre = 0.84; α Post = 0.84; α 3-Month Follow-up = 0.83; α 6-Month Follow-up = 0.81).PROMIS ® (v1.0) short form versions were used to assess sleep disturbance (6 items), alcohol use (7 items), alcohol use negative consequences (7 items), and depression (6 items).",
    "PROMIS measures have variable ranges (sleep disturbance, alcohol use, alcohol use negative consequences, anxiety, and depression), with higher scores indicating a higher rate of the measured outcome."
